1. PASSES

  The first pass is used to convert the source into a set of tokens.
  The second pass splits the tokens into multiple sections, errors may already be thrown here.
  On the third pass:
    1. All encountered labels get registered with their respective address.
    2. All instructions are attempted to be assembled.
    3. All usages of section names and already declared labels are replaced with their address.
    4. All usages of labels which are not declared at the point where they are used are marked
       for replacement.
  After the third pass, every label usage which could previously not be resolved is attempted to
  be resolved.